He tweeted that there would be a "strong turnout" of Tories at Prime Minister's Questions yesterday to prove they were not the unidentified man, who has been told to stay away. "I'll be there!" Mr Fabricant added, followed by the "winking face with tongue" emoji. He defended the tweet after a dressing-down by Tory whips, but later deleted the post. Welsh Secretary Simon Hart told BBC Politics Live: "It's idiotic, it's insensitive, and it attempts to make light of a really serious situation. "I despair when I read stuff like that." Deputy Labour leader Angela Rayner said it was "grotesque", while shadow health secretary Wes Streeting warned "this isn't a joke". Chris Bryant added: "This shows absolutely shameful disregard for the alleged victims." 